      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "JACKS ULTIMATE FURY NZ (7) comes off a strong showing in a good field at Maryborough last start where he raced parked but stuck on for fourth behind last year's Eureka winner Bay Of Biscay. Draws wider but should be approaching peak fitness and this race suits. SOHO PARK AVENUE (3) has been freshened since the Gold Chalice series where he was runner-up in the heats before drawing poorly in the final. Had wide barriers in the NSW Derby series here prior but performed well, placing in his heat. Aided by this draw and should be ready off a trial. LOUIE LOU I NZ (11) cops the outside barrier but looks close to a win having twice finished second at this circuit and distance before racing parked but sticking on for a 4.4m fourth last week. VINCENZO (10) made an encouraging first appearance for David Thorn when beaten only 2.2m into second from a similar barrier. Should strip fitter. LETS TURN IT ON (2) added to a good fresh record when runner-up last week and draws lower.",
